# Git identity (always)

All Neko commits **must** use:

```
rokiai <vnues.wgf@gmail.com>
```

- Commit: `git commit --author="rokiai <vnues.wgf@gmail.com>" …`
- `pnpm version`: set `GIT_AUTHOR_NAME` / `GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL` / `GIT_COMMITTER_*` for that command only
- **Do not** change `git config user.name` / `user.email`

## Remotes

| Remote   | Role                                      |
| -------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| `origin` | GitHub — primary, CI / Releases           |
| `gitee`  | Gitee — mirror                            |

When pushing / syncing: push **both** `origin` and `gitee`, then keep `main` tracking `origin/main`.

Full workflows: `.cursor/skills/neko-commit/SKILL.md`, `.cursor/skills/neko-release/SKILL.md`
